🔥 PURPOSE OF EACH (very important)

🟦 TOOL CALLING

Purpose: Let LLM use Python functions.

Use when:

	•	user input is unpredictable

	•	LLM must decide

	•	multi-tool usage possible

⸻

🟩 AGENTS

Purpose: Add REASONING + PLANNING on top of tool calling.

Use when:

	•	many tools

	•	multi-step decisions

	•	dynamic tasks

	•	user can ask ANYTHING

Agent = tool calling + reasoning brain

⸻

🟥 WORKFLOWS / PIPELINES

Purpose: Execute business logic in FIXED order.

Use when:

	•	enterprise workflows

	•	underwriting

	•	claims validation

	•	document extraction

	•	compliance

	•	deterministic processing

Workflow = predictable, controlled, no “surprises.”

⸻

🧠 FINAL SUMMARY (Read this twice)

Feature	Tool Calling	Agents	Workflow/Pipeline

Who decides?	LLM	LLM with reasoning	Developer

Order of steps	Dynamic	Dynamic	Fixed

Good for	Chat, simple tools	AI assistants	Business processes

Calls tools?	Yes	Yes	Optional

Can branch?	No	Yes	Yes (conditional)

Can loop?	No	Yes	Limited


